    <p>
      Most days, I'm in front of a whiteboard or a terminal trying to show
      someone why their GenAI application is a black box — and how to make
      it not one. Traces, latency, cost, model behavior, the whole picture.
      I'm a Sales Engineer at Datadog, which is a fancy way of saying I get
      to nerd out about observability for a living and occasionally get on
      a stage to talk about it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Off the clock, I'm based in Massachusetts with my wife, our two kids, and
    whatever half-finished hobby I've picked up that month. I grew up in
    India, spent a couple of years working there before moving to Boston
    for a master's at Northeastern — so a good chunk of what shows up
    here traces back to that place one way or another, whether it's a
    work trip, a family visit that ran long, or just something I miss
    about it.
  </p>

  <p>
    This site is where the shiptalk, the wanderlog, and the sidequests
